<headline>Winter Storm Watch issued December 14 at 2:42PM EST until December 17 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH
SATURDAY MORNING...
* WHAT...Heavy, wet snow possible. Snow accumulations will vary
with elevation. The best chance for 6 inches or more over
higher elevations. Winds could gust as high as 35 mph.
* WHERE...Hartford CT County, mainly in the highest elevations
northwest of I-84.
* WHEN...From Thursday afternoon through Saturday morning.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.</description>
<instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.</instruction>
